SENATE JOINT RESOLUTION—Urging Congress to enact
legislation allowing certain eligible surviving spouses of
veterans to receive an amount equal to the military
retirement pay of the veteran after the veteran’s death.
1 WHEREAS, Certain veterans who serve in the Armed Forces of
2 the United States for a period of at least 20 years or who qualify to
3 retire medically are eligible to receive military retirement pay for
4 their military service; and
5 WHEREAS, Military retirement pay, however, terminates upon
6 the death of the veteran, so many veterans enroll in the Survivor
7 Benefit Plan, which was enacted by Congress in 1972 and which
8 provides a monetary benefit in the form of a lifetime annuity to the
9 surviving spouse or other beneficiary of the veteran upon the
10 veteran’s death; and
11 WHEREAS, A portion of the cost of this annuity is paid from
12 reductions to the veteran’s retirement pay, and the maximum
13 survivor benefit is 55 percent of the retirement pay of the veteran at
14 the time of the veteran’s death; and
